        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: import historical call events",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #256 by importing WhatsApp call-log records from the paths that carry completed historical calls, not just live call signaling events.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Fetch the `regular` app-state collection as a snapshot during sync so existing call-log records are replayed and stored idempotently.\n- Parse and store `HistorySync.callLogRecords` when WhatsApp includes call logs in history sync payloads.\n- Add an experimental `history full-sync --call-logs` command plus `auth --full-history` capability advertising for accounts that can request full-history-on-demand.\n- Parse full-history peer responses so accepted/rejected/timeout cases are visible instead of silently waiting.\n- Fix call-log data quality:\n  - app-state `startTime` can be seconds, not only milliseconds\n  - call records use the linked-device LID as the self identity\n  - re-importing the same call updates corrected timestamp/chat fields instead of leaving stale bad rows\n\n## Root cause\n\n`calls list` was mostly showing live `offer` events because completed call logs arrive through WhatsApp app-state/history structures. The `regular` app-state collection was not replayed, and earlier imports also decoded app-state call timestamps/self identity incorrectly.\n\n## Local verification\n\n- `go test ./internal/app ./internal/wa ./internal/store ./cmd/wacli`\n- `pnpm format:check && pnpm lint && pnpm test && pnpm build && git diff --check`\n- Live local sync after the fix imported today’s completed call as a `call_log` row with the correct peer chat, timestamp, duration, direction, media, and outcome.\n",
